19
00:02:04,124 --> 00:02:05,083
Hey!

20
00:02:06,668 --> 00:02:09,379
YOUNGSAN EXPRESS BUS TERMINAL

21
00:02:19,056 --> 00:02:20,223
LEGAL NAME CHANGE FORM

22
00:02:20,307 --> 00:02:21,308
<i><font color="white">And</font></i>

23
00:02:22,184 --> 00:02:23,185
<i><font color="white">I heard…</font></i>

24
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:26,480
NEW NAME
KIM HYE-JOO

25
00:02:26,563 --> 00:02:28,190
<i><font color="white">…that name again…</font></i>

26
00:02:28,273 --> 00:02:29,566
Kim Jae-eun.

27
00:02:31,568 --> 00:02:34,571
<i><font color="white">…for the first time in 20 years.</font></i>

28
00:02:35,739 --> 00:02:36,615
Or should I say…

29
00:02:37,282 --> 00:02:38,200
Kim Hye-joo?

30
00:02:45,082 --> 00:02:46,249
You murderer.

31
00:02:58,762 --> 00:03:00,722
CONFRONTATION

32
00:03:02,766 --> 00:03:03,642
How have you been?

33
00:03:05,435 --> 00:03:06,436
Right.

34
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:08,605
I know it's late,
but congratulations on your marriage.

35
00:03:09,648 --> 00:03:11,400
The wife of an assemblyman?

36
00:03:12,275 --> 00:03:13,276
That's amazing.

37
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:24,329
You had reached out to my chief advisor

38
00:03:24,913 --> 00:03:27,416
but I wanted to meet you personally.

39
00:03:32,629 --> 00:03:33,839
Look…

40
00:03:33,922 --> 00:03:35,257
Is that your daughter?

41
00:03:35,340 --> 00:03:36,466
No.

42
00:03:37,342 --> 00:03:38,385
Then who is she?

43
00:03:42,389 --> 00:03:43,348
She's a kid I know.

44
00:03:48,270 --> 00:03:51,314
Yes, she's just a kid I know.

45
00:03:53,191 --> 00:03:54,317
Look, Seung-hee.

46
00:03:56,111 --> 00:03:58,155
I'm a bit busy today,

47
00:03:58,697 --> 00:03:59,698
so let's talk…

48
00:04:00,615 --> 00:04:02,284
Let's talk another time, okay?

49
00:04:06,079 --> 00:04:06,997
All right.

50
00:04:08,623 --> 00:04:10,250
Let me get your number then.

51
00:04:10,876 --> 00:04:12,002
Sure.

52
00:04:29,686 --> 00:04:30,979
Save my number.

53
00:04:31,813 --> 00:04:32,773
I'll call you.

54
00:04:35,650 --> 00:04:36,777
Okay.

55
00:04:39,154 --> 00:04:40,572
It's so nice to see you.

56
00:04:46,077 --> 00:04:47,329
I missed you,

57
00:04:48,413 --> 00:04:49,331
my friend.

58
00:04:53,168 --> 00:04:54,377
See you later.

59
00:05:05,972 --> 00:05:07,015
Ms. Kim.

60
00:05:08,517 --> 00:05:09,351
Ms. Kim.

61
00:05:13,647 --> 00:05:17,359
Let's visit Ji-hoon some other time.

62
00:05:17,943 --> 00:05:20,529
I'm feeling unwell.
I need to get some rest.

63
00:05:30,497 --> 00:05:31,331
<i><font color="white">What?</font></i>

64
00:05:31,414 --> 00:05:32,249
My name?

65
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:33,333
Yes.

66
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:36,169
I'm taking out a mortgage
to fund the election campaign.

67
00:05:36,753 --> 00:05:38,213
I needed our resident registration forms

68
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:40,215
since the house
is under both of our names,

69
00:05:40,298 --> 00:05:42,300
and yours said you had changed your name.

70
00:05:42,926 --> 00:05:43,760
Kim Jae-eun?

71
00:05:44,636 --> 00:05:46,596
It's a pretty name. Why did you change it?

72
00:05:49,099 --> 00:05:50,267
No reason.

73
00:05:51,518 --> 00:05:52,686
"Kim Jae-eun."

74
00:05:53,937 --> 00:05:55,188
That's new.

75
00:05:56,314 --> 00:05:57,148
Go to bed first.

76
00:05:57,732 --> 00:05:58,942
I'll be in the study.

77
00:06:16,585 --> 00:06:18,712
Thank you for reaching out to us.

78
00:06:21,506 --> 00:06:25,010
I came here to tell you
to stop what you're doing.

79
00:06:25,885 --> 00:06:28,513
My mother-in-law has done nothing wrong.

80
00:06:29,848 --> 00:06:31,600
We can get into that later.

81
00:06:32,350 --> 00:06:34,311
Are you originally from Youngsan?

82
00:06:34,894 --> 00:06:36,730
It's also my wife's hometown.

83
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:39,107
I see.

84
00:06:41,651 --> 00:06:44,779
She often talks about
fond memories of Youngsan,

85
00:06:44,863 --> 00:06:48,867
so whenever I meet people from there,
I feel at home as well.

86
00:06:49,492 --> 00:06:52,495
But I try to stay professional

87
00:06:52,579 --> 00:06:54,039
and distinguish

88
00:06:54,873 --> 00:06:56,166
right from wrong.

89
00:07:10,513 --> 00:07:13,266
Now that we're acquainted,
try to arrange a meal with him.

90
00:07:15,769 --> 00:07:16,811
What are you doing?

91
00:07:18,647 --> 00:07:20,774
Sir, it's about Ji Seung-kyu's family.

92
00:07:21,650 --> 00:07:22,692
Ji Seung…

93
00:07:22,776 --> 00:07:24,611
Right, the medical student? What is it?

94
00:07:26,571 --> 00:07:28,949
His mother swallowed some pills.

95
00:07:36,790 --> 00:07:41,002
Do you think Mr. Nam's meeting
with Mr. Choi didn't go very well?

96
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:43,213
He's been looking kind of uneasy.

97
00:07:43,838 --> 00:07:44,839
Right?

98
00:07:45,465 --> 00:07:47,175
What could it be?

99
00:07:49,010 --> 00:07:50,220
ASSEMBLYMAN'S OFFICE

100
00:07:50,303 --> 00:07:51,638
Thanks. Bye.

101
00:07:56,559 --> 00:07:59,270
They pumped her stomach,
so her life is not in danger.

102
00:08:02,983 --> 00:08:04,150
Why did she do it?

103
00:08:06,444 --> 00:08:07,404
I'm not sure.

104
00:08:07,487 --> 00:08:08,321
Well…

105
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:11,992
She must be either heartbroken
over the loss of her son

106
00:08:12,075 --> 00:08:13,702
or shocked by the hateful comments.

107
00:08:14,744 --> 00:08:18,790
Every article about him had quite a few
comments saying that he deserved to die.

108
00:08:22,585 --> 00:08:24,963
I called them "hateful comments",

109
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:27,340
but that's the public sentiment.

110
00:08:28,091 --> 00:08:30,093
So please don't blame yourself

111
00:08:30,677 --> 00:08:32,971
for what happened to him or his mother.

112
00:08:40,478 --> 00:08:42,689
Are you thinking about Ji-hoon?

113
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:47,027
How could I not?

114
00:08:48,194 --> 00:08:50,864
He must have received
tens of thousands of hate comments.

115
00:08:51,614 --> 00:08:53,324
Every time he did something wrong

116
00:08:53,908 --> 00:08:55,744
and even after his death.

117
00:08:57,954 --> 00:08:59,998
It's true that what he did was wrong,

118
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:03,668
and he should be scolded
and punished for it.

119
00:09:06,713 --> 00:09:08,006
But…

120
00:09:08,089 --> 00:09:10,675
NAM JOONG-DO MUST TAKE RESPONSIBILITY
FOR HIS SON'S MISDEEDS AND STEP DOWN

121
00:09:12,510 --> 00:09:14,220
<i><font color="white">Most parents beg for mercy</font></i>

122
00:09:14,888 --> 00:09:18,016
<i><font color="white">when their children do something wrong…</font></i>

123
00:09:18,099 --> 00:09:21,394
I ask for him to be punished
strictly by the law,

124
00:09:21,478 --> 00:09:24,355
and I sincerely apologize as his father

125
00:09:25,023 --> 00:09:26,775
for failing to discipline him properly.

126
00:09:26,858 --> 00:09:28,276
THE NATIONAL ASSEMBLY
OF THE REPUBLIC OF KOREA

127
00:09:29,652 --> 00:09:31,446
<i><font color="white">…but I did the opposite.</font></i>

128
00:09:33,073 --> 00:09:34,032
Hi, honey.

129
00:09:42,499 --> 00:09:46,544
NAM APOLOGIZES FOR SON'S ASSAULT CASE
AT PRESS CONFERENCE

130
00:09:50,799 --> 00:09:52,884
<i><font color="white">And it hurt my wife greatly.</font></i>

131
00:09:58,306 --> 00:10:00,141
Don't give a criminal a narrative.

132
00:10:03,728 --> 00:10:04,813
What?

133
00:10:06,689 --> 00:10:08,483
"Don't give a criminal a narrative."

134
00:10:09,025 --> 00:10:11,444
That's what the audience says these days

135
00:10:12,028 --> 00:10:15,240
when characters in movies or dramas
say something like that.

136
00:10:16,157 --> 00:10:19,327
They refuse to give criminals
any room for pity

137
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:21,079
or being understood.

138
00:10:21,704 --> 00:10:23,164
That's the public sentiment.

139
00:10:25,583 --> 00:10:28,211
I have a heavy heart
whenever I think of Ji-hoon,

140
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:30,463
but that's the reality.

141
00:10:32,507 --> 00:10:34,384
What I mean by that is,

142
00:10:34,467 --> 00:10:37,428
you have to keep your pity,
or any form of personal sentiments

143
00:10:37,512 --> 00:10:40,056
toward Ji-hoon or
Ji Seung-kyu's mother, at home.

144
00:10:40,557 --> 00:10:42,517
You should only express it to your wife.

145
00:10:43,643 --> 00:10:45,979
You're not Ji-hoon's father right now.

146
00:10:46,062 --> 00:10:48,273
You're an assemblyman
with an election coming up.

147
00:10:48,857 --> 00:10:51,192
Just like you said,
you have to stay professional.

148
00:11:15,216 --> 00:11:16,801
If you were to lose your child,

149
00:11:17,719 --> 00:11:19,804
what would you rather have
the cause of death be?

150
00:11:20,805 --> 00:11:23,182
Suicide, murder…

151
00:11:25,018 --> 00:11:26,269
or an accident?

152
00:11:30,231 --> 00:11:32,442
The last one would be the least painful.

153
00:11:38,448 --> 00:11:39,991
It would be, wouldn't it?

154
00:11:40,742 --> 00:11:41,826
Yes.

155
00:11:44,913 --> 00:11:46,289
At least as a parent.

156
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:04,474
<i><font color="white">She often talks about
fond memories of Youngsan,</font></i>

157
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:07,936
<i><font color="white">so whenever I meet people from there,
I feel at home as well.</font></i>

158
00:12:08,436 --> 00:12:10,355
-She ran away?
-Yes.

159
00:12:10,939 --> 00:12:13,232
She left town as soon as she graduated.

160
00:12:13,316 --> 00:12:15,652
She ran away from her crimes.

161
00:12:29,123 --> 00:12:30,458
SEOUL TO YOUNGSAN

162
00:12:38,633 --> 00:12:41,844
KIM JAE-EUN

163
00:12:54,148 --> 00:12:56,526
You've been living
a happy life, haven't you?

164
00:13:39,861 --> 00:13:41,654
NEW MESSAGE FROM SEUNG-HEE

165
00:13:45,867 --> 00:13:47,326
MEDICAL STUDENT COMMITS SUICIDE
AFTER BEING EXPOSED BY NAM

166
00:13:49,829 --> 00:13:51,497
<i><font color="white">Your husband killed someone as well.</font></i>

167
00:13:53,332 --> 00:13:54,584
<i><font color="white">By the way,</font></i>

168
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:56,419
<i><font color="white">does he know about your past?</font></i>

169
00:14:10,683 --> 00:14:12,310
INCOMING CALL

170
00:14:16,731 --> 00:14:18,608
-Hey, Seung-hee.
<i><font color="white">-I saw the news.</font></i>

171
00:14:21,194 --> 00:14:22,236
Hey.

172
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:23,362
Look, Seung-hee…

173
00:14:23,446 --> 00:14:25,114
<i><font color="white">Did you think fleeing to Seoul
and changing your name</font></i>

174
00:14:25,698 --> 00:14:28,076
would cover up the murder you committed?

175
00:14:29,243 --> 00:14:32,997
<i><font color="white">If that's what you wanted,
you should have kept a low profile.</font></i>

176
00:14:33,081 --> 00:14:34,791
<i><font color="white">Did you think no one would recognize you</font></i>

177
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:37,627
when you're the wife of an assemblyman?

178
00:14:40,838 --> 00:14:42,006
<i><font color="white">Come to Youngsan.</font></i>

179
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:43,674
<i><font color="white">We should…</font></i>

180
00:14:44,592 --> 00:14:46,052
<i><font color="white">continue our little chat.</font></i>

181
00:14:48,513 --> 00:14:50,139
Come here tomorrow.

182
00:14:50,807 --> 00:14:52,767
And don't even think about running away.

183
00:14:54,769 --> 00:14:57,021
Seung-hee--

184
00:15:06,114 --> 00:15:08,449
YOUR HUSBAND KILLED SOMEONE AS WELL.
DOES HE KNOW ABOUT YOUR PAST?

185
00:15:22,797 --> 00:15:23,798
Mom.

186
00:15:26,259 --> 00:15:27,552
Mom.

187
00:15:27,635 --> 00:15:29,178
Hey, I'm home.

188
00:15:30,596 --> 00:15:33,349
Where have you been all day?

189
00:15:34,350 --> 00:15:35,518
Sorry.

190
00:15:35,601 --> 00:15:36,686
I had to take care of something.

191
00:15:38,521 --> 00:15:39,772
Mom.

192
00:15:41,357 --> 00:15:43,025
What is it?

193
00:15:43,109 --> 00:15:44,444
Well…

194
00:15:44,527 --> 00:15:47,238
I know we're supposed to go
shopping for land tomorrow,

195
00:15:48,072 --> 00:15:49,323
but can you go without me?

196
00:15:50,158 --> 00:15:50,992
Why?

197
00:15:51,909 --> 00:15:53,077
Something's come up.

198
00:15:53,995 --> 00:15:56,622
You're meeting your friends
in the evening anyway.

199
00:15:57,206 --> 00:15:58,958
I'll go with you next time, okay?

200
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:00,710
Just for tomorrow.

201
00:16:01,377 --> 00:16:03,421
I wouldn't be of much help anyway.

202
00:16:06,674 --> 00:16:09,010
Hey, is Ki-young home yet?

203
00:16:13,139 --> 00:16:14,182
"Ki-young"?

204
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:18,644
You come home
after spending the entire day out,

205
00:16:18,728 --> 00:16:21,731
and the first person
you ask about is your husband?

206
00:16:22,648 --> 00:16:26,694
Are you not worried about me
who's been at home all alone?

207
00:16:27,653 --> 00:16:32,325
You two should have just gone
to live in Australia without me.

208
00:16:36,037 --> 00:16:37,038
Mom.

209
00:16:37,788 --> 00:16:39,790
Could you please stop saying that?

210
00:16:39,874 --> 00:16:43,252
I'm really sorry for saying
I wanted to move to Australia.

211
00:16:43,336 --> 00:16:45,505
But I didn't go. So please--

212
00:16:45,588 --> 00:16:46,756
I don't want to hear it.

213
00:16:47,757 --> 00:16:51,177
You're the only child I have left
after Seung-ho passed away,

214
00:16:52,220 --> 00:16:55,014
but I don't want to talk
to a heartless person like you anymore.

215
00:16:55,723 --> 00:16:58,017
I'll go by myself tomorrow.

216
00:16:58,100 --> 00:17:00,686
And I'll drop dead right there

217
00:17:00,770 --> 00:17:02,355
-and go meet Seung-ho.
-Mom.

218
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:06,901
Fine.

219
00:17:06,984 --> 00:17:08,361
I'll come with you, okay?

220
00:17:08,444 --> 00:17:10,238
I'm sorry about everything
and I'll come with you.

221
00:17:10,821 --> 00:17:12,949
So please just stop it, will you?

222
00:17:24,001 --> 00:17:25,962
COME TO THIS ADDRESS

223
00:17:31,008 --> 00:17:34,011
<i><font color="white">Come to this address at 7 p.m. tomorrow.</font></i>

224
00:17:36,764 --> 00:17:37,682
<i><font color="white">You murderer.</font></i>

225
00:17:48,776 --> 00:17:49,902
DELETE

226
00:17:50,736 --> 00:17:51,696
